title: Cowboy Junkies 1996-04-15 @ 930 Club - Washington, D.C
description:
So, this show comes from the Lay It Down tour, an always special one. Of course, most of you seem to prefer to see the older shows released anyway, so that isn&#039;t all that surprising.

 

The recording here has got some great performances. At one point, Margo quips to the audience, "I don&#039;t think Mike has played this well all tour." "Just Want to See" has a great energy to it, and the "Powerfinger" is beautifully solemn.

 

I&#039;ve always felt that "Something More Besides You" is one the best songs the band has ever done, proven by how good it sounds both electric and acoustic. It&#039;s actually one of my four favorite Junkies&#039; songs (the others are "Ring on the Sill," "Witches," and "Notes Falling Slow.") Here again, Mike shines, and the "Working on a Building" is a perfect closer to an excellent show.
